descript.abstract: The Breachline Master Template uses a geospatial database template (i.e. with empty feature classes and tables) designed to contain breachlines developed in Minnesota for use in DEM hydro-modification and terrain analysis. The template is designed to help entites standardize and manage their breachlines. In addition, the template puts the data into a consistent, standardized form that makes it more readily accessible to users such as hydrologists and gis specialists.
descript.supplinf: State of Minnesota and bordering watersheds
descript.purpose: This data and database template will be used for collection in order to have a standardized database of breachlines for use in hydro-modification.

attr.attrdef: Identifies the source of the data that was used in the placement of the breachline
The type of feature that the breachline represents in the digital elevation model (DEM)

Breachlines are digitzed based on their relation to the underlying DEM cell resolution size. This field identifies the cell resoltion that the breachline was digitized from and the resolution that is suggested these breachlines be used on.

The confidence rating is essentially a database attribute tracking the evaluation of how well a digital dam breachline will serve the hDEM hydro-modification process and resulting hDEM flow path development.
